🔹 1. Human languages supported by Java (Localization)

Java supports many human languages using built-in features like Locale and ResourceBundle.

Examples of supported languages:
English
Hindi
Malayalam
Arabic
French
German
Chinese
Japanese

👉 Java uses:

Locale → to represent language & region
ResourceBundle → to load translated text

✔ This is used in apps that show different languages to users.

🔹 2. Programming languages that run on Java (JVM languages)

Java runs on the JVM (Java Virtual Machine), and many other languages can also run on it.

Popular JVM-supported languages:
Java (main language)
Kotlin → used for Android development
Scala → used in big data & functional programming
Groovy → scripting language
Clojure → functional language
JRuby → Ruby on JVM
Jython → Python on JVM
🔹 Why multiple languages?

👉 Because JVM allows:

Compile different languages → convert to bytecode
JVM runs that bytecode

✔ So Java is not just a language
✔ It’s a platform
